  "text": "Despite these limitations, we believe that these factors did not seriously impair the results, for the following reasons. First, if a selection bias did distort the results it probably did not change the direction of the associations found, as results in the companion survey in a random sample of Italian citizens results were very similar. [CITATION_1] Secondly, we carried out further analyses to test whether people receiving help answered in systematically different ways: we checked the distribution of the help across the main categories, and then introduced this variable into the model. The findings did not change at all.",
